    "vl_rich_text_RJwVCQ": {
      "type": "vl-rich-text",
      "name": "VL Rich Text",
      "settings": {
        "subheading": "First Impressions",
        "content": "<p>The first thing you notice about the Vera Lane Tone Adapting Foundation is its unusual white-to-pink appearance in the tube. It's a bit unnerving if you're used to picking a shade from a lineup — there's only one shade here, and it claims to match everyone.</p><p>The texture is lightweight, almost serum-like. It doesn't feel heavy or greasy the way many full-coverage foundations do. When you pump a small amount onto the back of your hand, the color begins shifting within about 30 seconds — responding to your skin's natural pH and warmth.</p><p>The packaging itself is simple and clean. No overwrought branding or excessive claims on the bottle. It feels like a product that's confident enough to let results speak for themselves. The pump dispenses a controlled amount, which is helpful when you're building coverage.</p>",
        "bg_color": "#ffffff",
        "heading_color": "#000000",
        "text_color": "#333333",
        "link_color": "#5C1A33"
      }
    },
    "vl_image_text_GOSGm2": {
      "type": "vl-image-text",
      "name": "VL Image + Text",
      "settings": {
        "image": "shopify://shop_images/Tone_Adapting_Foundation_Makeup_brush_-_Image_3.jpg",
        "image_alt": "Vera Lane Tone Adapting Foundation texture close-up",
        "image_caption": "The satin-matte finish sits naturally on mature skin without emphasising dry patches.",
        "heading": "Coverage & Texture",
        "text": "<p>This is where the Vera Lane foundation really earns its keep. One thin layer gives you a natural, skin-like finish that evens out tone without looking like you're wearing foundation at all. Two layers build to a medium coverage that conceals redness, sun spots, and minor hyperpigmentation without caking.</p><p>The texture stays smooth once applied — it doesn't get patchy or separate as the day goes on. For mature skin, that's not a small thing.</p>",
        "bg_color": "#ffffff",
        "heading_color": "#000000",
        "text_color": "#333333"
      }
    },
    "vl_rich_text_WYCkHa": {
      "type": "vl-rich-text",
      "name": "VL Rich Text",
      "settings": {
        "subheading": "",
        "content": "<p>Many foundations that look beautiful at 8am start breaking down by noon, collecting in creases around the eyes and mouth. This one held up remarkably well.</p><p><strong>The finish is satin-matte</strong> — not dewy enough to look oily, not matte enough to emphasise dry patches. It's that rare middle ground that works well on skin that's lost some of its natural moisture with age. Over moisturised skin, it looked genuinely luminous without being shiny.</p>",
        "bg_color": "#ffffff",
        "heading_color": "#000000",
        "text_color": "#333333",
        "link_color": "#5C1A33"
      }
    },
    "vl_pull_quote_oCsrYU": {
      "type": "vl-pull-quote",
      "name": "VL Pull Quote",
      "settings": {
        "quote": "After testing dozens of foundations marketed to women over 40, this is the first one that actually looked better at the end of the day than at the start.",
        "attribution": "— Our Testing Team",
        "bg_color": "#F5EDE8",
